attributes.content: Africa Oil Corp. was incorporated under the BC BCA on March 29, 1993 under the name ‘Canmex Minerals Corporation’ with an authorized capital of 100,000,000 common shares. On July 2, 1999 the issued and outstanding common shares of the Company were consolidated on a one-for-five basis and the authorized capital was increased, post-consolidation from 20,000,000 to 100,000,000 common shares.

body.value: Africa Oil Corp. was incorporated under the BC BCA on March 29, 1993 under the name ‘Canmex Minerals Corporation’ with an authorized capital of 100,000,000 common shares. On July 2, 1999 the issued and outstanding common shares of the Company were consolidated on a one-for-five basis and the authorized capital was increased, post-consolidation from 20,000,000 to 100,000,000 common shares. On August 20, 2007 the Company changed its name to ‘Africa Oil Corp.’ On June 19, 2009, the shareholders of the Company passed a special resolution increasing the Company’s authorized share capital to an unlimited number of common shares. On June 3, 2013, the shareholders of Africa Oil passed a special resolution authorizing an alteration of the Company’s articles to include advance notice provisions for the nomination of directors.

Afrochine Smelting P/L accomplished the construction of 2 x 16.5MVA smelters with a capacity to produce 50,000 metric tons of ferrochrome per year, as the first phase of the project. These smelters are being constructed in Selous, which is located about 80km from the capital Harare.

body.value: Afrochine Smelting (Pvt) Ltd was established in 2012 and is a subsidiary of China’s second-biggest stainless steel products manufacturer Tsingshan Group. The company is currently setting up a state of the art ferrochrome smelting plant in Selous. Afrochine Smelting P/L accomplished the construction of 2 x 16.5MVA smelters with a capacity to produce 50,000 metric tons of ferrochrome per year, as the first phase of the project. attributes.content: Aqua Construction Limited is a family-run construction company delivering sustainable yet individual housing projects throughout Gloucestershire for both registered providers of social housing and private clients.

body.value:
Aqua Construction Limited is a family-run construction company delivering sustainable yet individual housing projects throughout Gloucestershire for both registered providers of social housing and private clients.

The business was established in 1998 by Jason Wasley after he had gained extensive experience running development projects of various sizes around the world. Since then, a team of highly experienced and qualified individuals from a range of trades has been assembled to enable an integrated approach to the design and build of houses. From plumbers to bricklayers, carpenters to engineers, Aqua Construction brings a wide range of skills to bear on every project. In addition, a reliable supply chain has been established, consisting of key supplier and sub-contractor partners, accustomed to working together and focussed on delivering high quality homes within a range of budgets and timeframes.

attributes.content: On the 4th March 1957, just two days before the declaration of political independence, the Bank of Ghana was formally established by the Bank of Ghana Ordinance (No. 34) of 1957, passed by the British Parliament. Frantic preparations then began to put in place an organisational structure for the new central bank. By the middle of July 1957, all was set for the official commissioning of the new Head Office of the Bank on the High Street.

body.value: On the 4th March 1957, just two days before the declaration of political independence, the Bank of Ghana was formally established by the Bank of Ghana Ordinance (No. 34) of 1957, passed by the British Parliament. Frantic preparations then began to put in place an organisational structure for the new central bank. By the middle of July 1957, all was set for the official commissioning of the new Head Office of the Bank on the High Street. The principal objects of the new central bank, as enshrined in the 1957 Ordinance, were "to issue and redeem bank notes and coins: to keep and use reserves and to influence the credit situation with a view to maintaining monetary stability in Ghana and the external value of the Ghana pound; and to act as banker and financial adviser to the Government.

attributes.content: The Central Bank of Ghana traces its roots to the Bank of the Gold Coast (BCG), where it was nurtured. As soon as local politicians and economists saw political independence in sight in the mid 1950's the agitation for a central bank was revived. It was argued that a central bank was one institution which would give true meaning to political independence. It may be recalled that way back in 1947 some leading politicians had called for the establishment of a national bank with central bank functions to act as banker to government and to cater for the indigenous sector of the economy.

attributes.name: description
attributes.content: DEROU & PARTNERS is an international design office established on January 1, 2004, by Arch. Dontou Hiloukou DEROU, trained at EAMAU in Togo and the School of Architecture of Nancy in France. The firm's philosophy, applied to projects in over a dozen African countries, focuses on human comfort and the evolution of architecture, emphasizing constant innovation. The firm operates with a multidisciplinary team, where each member feels responsible for every study, ensuring a global understanding of each project.
